  <title>Who was the better offensive coach in Real Madrid</title>
  <dc:creator>Noora Mohamed</dc:creator>
  <link>https://your-website-url.example.com/posts/real-madrids-manager-woes/</link>
  <description><![CDATA[ 





<p>The results of a game, always comes back to what the coaches teach behind closed doors. Coaches are expected to train, discipline and prepare their athletes for every possibility in the field.</p>
<p>Fans focus on the winning and scoring, the real impact all comes back to the objective, planning and knowledge, that coaches implant in their players.</p>
<p>The scores of a single game, leads back to what the coach taught and how successfully the players executed that vision, revealing the ability the coach has when it comes to playing offense.</p>
<p>Álvaro Arbeloa-</p>
<p><a href="https://www.realmadrid.com/en-US/the-club/history/football-legends/alvaro-arbeloa-coca">Álvaro Arbeloa</a>, a Spanish former defender football player professional footballer and current manager. Arbeloa has won many trophies; Club World Cup, a UEFA Super Cup, a LaLiga Title, two Copas del Rey and a Spanish Super Cup. Shifting from a player into a coach, Arebola alongside his passion and management that highlighting his career.</p>
